## Camera state

```js
const camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
const cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
```

---

## Particle storage

```js
let streamParticles = [];
let tick = 0;
```

---

# Main helper

## Find node by id

```js
function getNode(id) {
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}
```

---

# Physics update

## 1. Node simulation

Readable reconstruction:

```js
function updateNodes() {
  // Pairwise attraction between every node pair
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      const dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      const dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;

      const force = config.attraction / (dist * dist);
      const fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      const fy = (dy / dist) * force;

      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // Spring forces
  for (let i = 0; i < links.length; i++) {
    const a = getNode(links[i].a);
    const b = getNode(links[i].b);
    if (!a || !b) continue;

    const dx = b.x - a.x;
    const dy = b.y - a.y;
    const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;

    const stretch = dist - links[i].rest;
    const force = (links[i].k || config.springCoeff) * stretch;

    a.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    a.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    b.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    b.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // Center drift + damping + integrate position
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.centerDrift;
    nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.centerDrift;

    nodes[i].vx *= config.amplification;
    nodes[i].vy *= config.amplification;

    nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
    nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
  }
}
```

### Important note
The “attraction” math as written causes motion based on relative vector direction. In a normal physical model, signs and naming might imply attraction/repulsion ambiguities depending on vector convention, but overall the system is intended to create a **dynamic clustered graph layout**.

---

## 2. Spawn stream particles

```js
function spawnStreamParticle() {
  if (streamParticles.length >= config.streamLimit) return;

  const node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  const angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  const speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * ROOT_HALF;

  streamParticles.push({
    x: node.x,
    y: node.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * PHI) * ROOT_HALF
  });
}
```

These particles are emitted from random node positions and drift outward.

---

## 3. Update particles

```js
function updateStreamParticles() {
  for (let i = streamParticles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    const p = streamParticles[i];

    p.age++;
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;

    p.vx *= (1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125);
    p.vy *= (1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125);

    if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
      streamParticles.splice(i, 1);
    }
  }
}
```

This gives particles a gradual slowdown and eventual removal.

---

## 4. Update camera

```js
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.theta;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.theta;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.theta;
}
```

That is a smooth lerp/easing camera.

---

## 5. Main tick

```js
function tickFrame() {
  updateNodes();
  updateStreamParticles();
  updateCamera();

  if (tick % 3 === 0) {
    spawnStreamParticle();
  }

  tick++;
}

setInterval(tickFrame, 10);
```

So:
- runs every 10ms
- updates nodes
- updates stream particles
- updates camera
- emits one particle every third tick

That means about:
- **100 updates/sec**
- about **33 particle spawns/sec**, capped at 40 particles

